[1
Date: 17 Dec 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: APOnline [edited
<http://www.newsday.com/news/nationworld/nation/wire/sns-ap-attacks-an
thrax1218dec17.story?coll=sns%2Dap%2Dnation%2Dheadlines>

Anthrax Probe Leads to U.S. Source [edited
----------------------------------------------
WASHINGTON -- The anthrax that killed 5 people appears to have been
produced in the United States, the White House said Monday, but
investigators still don't know who mailed it. White House press
secretary Ari Fleischer said the evidence on the anthrax sent to Sens.
Tom Daschle, D-S.D., and Patrick Leahy, D-Vt., is increasingly
"looking like it was a domestic source."
Technicians, meanwhile, ran into more problems trying to sanitize a
Senate office building contaminated by lingering anthrax spores from
the letter sent to Daschle in mid-October. Attempts to pump poisonous
gas into the Hart Senate Office Building's ventilation system to kill
any remaining spores failed early Monday, said Capitol Police
spokesman Lt. Dan Nichols. He said a mechanical problem kept the gas
from reaching the saturation point [500 parts per million needed to
kill the spores.
[Byline: Laura Meckler, Associated Press Writer
