[3
Date: Sun 16 Dec 2001 09:58:08 +0100
From: Fredrik Elgh <fredrik.elgh@climi.umu.se>

I just read the most recent ProMED-mail posting about the origin of
the deliberately released anthrax spores. In this letter there were
references to 2 articles in sunspot.net. In the article from 13 Dec
2001 it says:
" ... Some of the anthrax produced by Dugway has matched the fine
particle size and extraordinary concentration of the powder mailed to
Senate Majority Leader Tom Daschle, estimated at close to 1 trillion
spores per gram, according to a government scientist.
In addition, the mailed anthrax is genetically indistinguishable from
the Ames strain used by the Army, the most sophisticated test methods
show. ..."
What information exists on the formulation of the fine anthrax spore
particles? Does the Army (Dugway proving ground and/or USAMRIID or
other US Army unit using this type of anthrax spores) weapons-grade
anthrax contain the same additives (silica?) as the deliberately
released anthrax? Nothing of that nature has been commented on so far.
--
Fredrik Elgh
<fredrik.elgh@climi.umu.se>
[Former US government bioweaponeer Bill Patrick has refused to comment
on whether or not there was silica in the mailed anthrax. - Mod.JW
[There is a good account of Paul Keim and his genomic work on the
following Los Angeles Times site:
<http://www.latimes.com/news/yahoo/la-000100028dec17.story?coll=la%2Dn
ewsaol%2Dheadlines>
We seem to have reached that place in the investigation where those
who know (the FBI) are wisely not talking, and those who don't are,
with finger pointing in every direction by journalists egged on by
their respective editors. The physical-chemical-biological
characteristics of the Daschle & Leahy powders must be thoroughly
known by now, thereby providing an excellent source signature for the
investigators. Until such time that there is a breakthrough, I propose
that this thread be paused. That will either provide a period of
decent quiet or perversely a reactive revelation. Either way we are
ahead. - Mod.MHJ
